==English==
==Noun phrase==
'''copy-number variant''' (plural ''copy-number variants''; abbreviated ''[[CNV]]'')
# {{genetics}} a DNA sequence 1000 [[nucleotide]]s in length or longer that is present a variable number of times as copies in a [[genome]] relative to a [[reference genome]]
